ygData.messageBody:
Yep, I get the same thing.

 Jack Whaley <jdwhaley@...> wrote:

Does anyone else get responses to messages like this one below?  I get one of
these back everytime I post to this list.

----------  Forwarded Message  ----------

Subject: re: your email message
Date: Wed, 25 Dec 2002 10:17:05 -0500
From: "Lyris ListManager" <lyris-admin@...>
To: jdwhaley@...

The following lines in your email message did not appear to be

Lyris ListManager commands and were skipped:
> One other thing I just thought about.  I did not fight for the Griffon
> Feather. I bought it from a vendor, as well as the Ruby.  I feel confident
> it is okay to use a bought Ruby, but not so confident about the Griffon
> Feather. Any thoughts?
> On Monday 23 December 2002 09:20, Rob LeBeau wrote:
>  -> You did not specify a valid mailing list name to join.
>
> >  I heard that maybe one of these DOES matter the order
> >  in which she is given things.
> > I will check a couple of resources to see if that is
> >  true and if there is any mention of the order.
> > It will help me too since I have a 32 level Human
> >  mage.
> > Will let you know
> > Rob

This email message is simply a notification of how Lyris ListManager
understood your email message.  If you want to resend your commands, send
them to lyris@...
